subject: Using sdbusplus::asio::getProperty
commitMessage:
Using sdbusplus::asio::getProperty

It simplifies a lot of code and after changing sdbusplus implementation
slightly reduces binary size if used together with:

https://gerrit.openbmc-project.xyz/c/openbmc/sdbusplus/+/49467

* Uncompressed size:    3033148 -> 3012164, -20984 B
* gzip compressed size: 1220586 -> 1214625, -5961 B

Tested:
- Redfish validator output is the same before and after the change

Change-Id: Ibe3227d3f4230de2363ba3d9396e51130c8240a5
Signed-off-by: Jonathan Doman <jonathan.doman@intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Krzysztof Grobelny <krzysztof.grobelny@intel.com>

Patch Set 6:

Just measured the binary impact of this this:

With this change:    840192 bytes xz compressed
Without this change: 844028 bytes xz compressed

or about a 0.5% reduction in binary size, which on its own, isn't a big deal, but considering at the same time we dropped 400 lines of overall diff that was essentially boilerplate, this change is a great improvement.

Lets get the "POC" removed from the commit message and run it through a test or two (Redfish service validator should be fine) then this should be good to go.

Ideally we should do this quickly, otherwise merge conflicts are going to be tough to stay ahead of.

I will revert it back to /*hostName*/ in next patchset.
Done

In case of existing get property people use variant with one type which always is set to some value.
https://godbolt.org/z/fcK5EWTEP

In case of getProperty it is done properly, to variant type is added extra type to determine if value is present (type expected is same as type on dbus).
https://godbolt.org/z/56dKsd1j9

If you take a look at the examples, one branch is optimized out. Which might be the reason why it produces bigger binary size.

It's a good point.

Maybe it's also the adding of another lambda layer to every call site that increases the size. Each lambda is its own unique type so wouldn't that double the template instantiations?

I tried to look at the machine code to understand it better, but the function names are stupendously complicated and impossible for me to follow.

Good point.

Before this change there was calls to async_method_call for "Get" and variant<std::string>. This changes it under the deck to std::variant<std::monostate, std::string>. It fixes dead code, but introduces additional code for this variant type. I will check if using common variant type will help with it.
This change looks unrelated?  Still seems to be using get_if, although the new code does look better.

Event service uses same function to fill report as telemetry service. Since getProperty is used fillReport doesn't take variant anymore as parameter. In this case source of data is from signal, so get_if needs to be performed.

It may look like it's unrelated, but this change is needed in this patch.
AH, I see it now.  Thanks for the clarification.  Fine as is.
